VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT chmod\s+(?:0?777|[augo]+\+[rwx]*w[rwx]*|a\+x)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:# intentional|# required|umask && MISSING:test|example|sample
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects chmod commands granting world-writable or globally executable permissions.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Overly Permissive chmod.
